com.trefis.partitioner

Class SortedGreedyDoublePartitioner

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.trefis.partitioner.AbstractDoublePartitioner
      • com.trefis.partitioner.GreedyDoublePartitioner
        • com.trefis.partitioner.SortedGreedyDoublePartitioner
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Partitioner<java.lang.Double,java.lang.Double>

    public class SortedGreedyDoublePartitioner
extends GreedyDoublePartitioner
    This is a partitioner that has been implemented with a greedy algorithm but sorts the data before it does the partitioning The default sort is ascending. It looks for available space first before creating another group. Though this may not be as optimal but it Big O notation is O(n) as it only loops through the items once.

                                                                                   java.lang.Double maxSum)
        Does a default ascending sort first before actually doing the partition Takes a list of values and divides them into groups. The resulting groups are such that the sum of the values in the subset are less than a provided maxSum.
